  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (da2392e 2023-03-22T00:04:12.437988019Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen no fork-url is specified (or when vm.createFork() is called but vm.selectFork() is not called), forge test fails with what looks like a revert, rather than indicating the true cause of the error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ forge test -vv\r\n[⠢] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n2023-03-22T00:56:55.399025Z ERROR forge::runner: setUp failed reason=\"EvmError: Revert\" contract=0x...\r\n```\r\n",
