    "body": "I'll see if I can make something minimal, but I think it will literally entail (1) starting a hardhat node and (2) attempting to run a test contract with `forge test` but without specifying a `--fork-url`\r\n\r\nI'll note that this behavior differs from when forge cannot connect to the node at all, in which case it issues:\r\n```\r\n2023-03-22T01:24:44.019229Z ERROR forge::runner: setUp failed reason=\"Could not instantiate forked environment with fork url: http://127.0.0.1:8545/\" contract=0x...\r\n```\r\n",
